We almost dined inside until my friend made the suggestion to eat on the rooftop. It was everything! They have these misty fans that kept it cool and added to the already festive ambiance. The food was amazing. The drinks were great. It’s definitely a vibe. I highly recommend this restaurant. Can’t wait to visit again!!

I messed up and didn't take pictures. Never go out when you too hungry lol. Anyway. Stooped by this restaurant today. Haven't been over here since the original hispanic food restaurant closed. None the less. Was fortunate enough to get the rooftop seating. Weather was perfect. Service was quick. Portions and food are good. I highly recommend the rum bbq wings and the jerk chicken entree. Also the bucket margarita was good. Wished it was more Frozen but it tasted good regardless

Dishes were hit or miss. The Conch Fritters were borderline burnt, the Cubano was so-so. The Toston Nachos were tasty, but a little misleading (Nachos with a few plantain chips-not tostones). The Shrimp Mofongo was very good as well as the Surf n Turf Burger (cooked perfectly). The service was EXCELLENT, and actually is what brought the rating up. Very friendly, professional & attentive.

I was excited about this place because the decor looked great and food smelled good. However, we never got a chance to try anything. We were seated in the center of the floor by the host station and no way we could not be seen. The host seated us with no menus. We waited 15 minutes no menu, no alcohol, no server to come greet us. As we waited we watched two women congregated at the host station with nothing to do but watch us and several other servers walk around. We finally grab someone attention and they just said okay and walked away to get someone. More time passed by and a guy came over to greet us. We have already pulled up the menu on our phones because we were starving and thirsty at this point. He took our orders and we waited for another 15 minutes and no water or drinks at our tablr. Eventually we just got up and left. This place must been lacking management as too many people working here and the restaurant is not at full capacity!
Horrible experience. No one came to serve us. We had to ask for someone and it still took them forever.

Delicious happy hour meals for a good price. I highly recommend the fish tacos, calamari, & steamed shrimp from the Happy Hour menu.  The crab cake sandwich from the regular menu was superb!  Laid back atmosphere with reggae music playing. Will definitely come back again.

Food was nice, but I don't like it when they come and bring the bill before the last person has finished their meal.

The service at this place was very disappointing. We went on a sunday afternoon, when the restaurant had customers but was not filled to capacity. The 2 bartenders in the rooftop bar did their utmost not to make eye contact with us and were really unfriendly. Finally, one of them took our order but seemed to be under the influence or was really hung over - had difficulty with everything! A few people waited for a while to get their attention, and left when no one showed any interest. Pity, since its such a great location!

Very good, nice service, the jerk chicken was delicious as the cocktail.

I don’t know who is kidding themselves on these reviews. Our food was pretty lame, only get a star because the potatoes weren’t totally flavorless. Many ingredients missing from our breakfast sandwich and the service was non existent even though we were the only ones in the restaurant. Total tourist trap, go somewhere else.

The place looks amazing. Lots of tables of different sizes AND a rooftop deck. The food was presented well, but did lack seasoning with all the fried dishes. The jerk chicken was very good though.

First time there it was excellent

So my wife was dogsitting down here in Eastern Market, so we decided to come by. The dining room was deserted BUT that is not indicative of the restaurant. It's not crazy obvious from the ground, but they have a cool rooftop bar that was jumping.  Our server was great, attentive but not smothering, extremely pleasant and knowledgeable about the menu.  My partner got shrimp (steamed, but chilled is also an option) and the fish tacos (which come with a salad or fries - she loved the honey/lime dressing) and I had the hot wings and the Cuban. She liked all of her food and I liked my wings. The only knock on this place was the Cuban. I'm from Tampa and I can be a bit snobby about Cuban sandwiches, so maybe I'm being overly critical, but I felt like it needed more mustard, the shredded pork was the wrong flavor/consistency, the ham was a bit too thick, and the bread smelled/tasted a bit like burnt oil.  My partner also got (and loved) the dark and stormy, which was also pretty reasonably priced.  Overall, the vibe was cool, the rooftop was fun, the service was great. I'll definitely be back, I just won't get the Cuban.

This place was new for me and I wasn't disappointed. Great food and atmosphere. They have a selection of frozen alcoholic beverages as well as a wide range of variety of foods and drinks to choose from. Upstairs and downstairs area, although upstairs was more of a vibrant louder vibe. Downstairs a bit more chilled. Definitely will be going back
Great food, friendly servers, one of my favorite places to visit for Caribbean food.
The cocktails are good and so are the apps.  Service was a little in the weeds though on the rooftop.
I enjoyed the Calypso wings (jerk dry rub) and the conch fritters. Only giving it 3 stars until I visit again to try more options. The atmosphere and staff were great.

The food was awesome. I got the snapper and my husband got the jerk chicken sandwich. Both were good and the ceviche was awesome.
